t. The major\naxes of the cluster elongations and of the BCGs agree within 30 degrees for 73%\nof our clusters at redshift z <= 0.9. Our results agree with the BCGs being\nmainly formed before redshift z=2. The alignment of the major axes of BCGs with\ntheir clusters agree with the general idea that BCGs form at the same time as\nclusters by accreting matter along the filaments of the cosmic web.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Feb 2021 15:31:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-12"}
